.TH FUCKOOREDOO 1 "November 2024" "fuckooredoo 1.0.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fuckooredoo \- Secure Torrent Downloader with Tor-based Anti-Throttling
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fuckooredoo
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fuckooredoo
is a powerful BitTorrent client designed to bypass ISP throttling through
Tor network routing and advanced traffic encryption. It provides complete
anonymity and prevents Deep Packet Inspection (DPI) from detecting torrent
traffic.
.PP
The application routes all BitTorrent traffic through the Tor network with
RC4/MSE encryption, making it impossible for ISPs to detect and throttle
torrent downloads. It features a modern CustomTkinter GUI interface with
real-time download statistics and multi-torrent management.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-headless
Run in headless mode without GUI (for servers and automation)
.TP
.B \-\-magnet \fIMAGNET_LINK\fR
Start download immediately with the specified magnet link (requires --headless)
.TP
.B \-\-torrent \fIFILE\fR
Start download immediately with the specified .torrent file (requires --headless)
.TP
.B \-\-download-dir \fIDIRECTORY\fR
Set custom download directory (default: ~/Downloads)
.TP
.B \-\-help, \-h
Display help message and exit
.TP
.B \-\-version, \-v
Display version information and exit
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Tor Network Routing
All traffic is routed through the Tor network for complete anonymization
.TP
.B RC4/MSE Encryption
Military-grade encryption on every BitTorrent connection
.TP
.B DPI Bypass
Deep Packet Inspection circumvention through traffic obfuscation
.TP
.B Traffic Randomization
Makes torrent traffic appear as regular HTTPS traffic
.TP
.B Multi-torrent Support
Download multiple torrents simultaneously with independent controls
.TP
.B Modern GUI
Beautiful dark-themed CustomTkinter interface with real-time statistics
.TP
.B Magnet Link Support
Direct magnet link handling and .torrent file support
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Tor
The Tor service must be running for the application to function properly.
Install and start Tor:
.PP
.nf
    sudo apt install tor
    sudo systemctl start tor
    sudo systemctl enable tor
.fi
.TP
.B Python 3.8+
Python 3.8 or higher with Tkinter support
.TP
.B libtorrent
Python libtorrent bindings (python3-libtorrent)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start with GUI:
.nf
    fuckooredoo
.fi
.TP
Headless mode with magnet link:
.nf
    fuckooredoo --headless --magnet "magnet:?xt=urn:btih:..."
.fi
.TP
Headless mode with .torrent file:
.nf
    fuckooredoo --headless --torrent /path/to/file.torrent
.fi
.TP
Custom download directory:
.nf
    fuckooredoo --download-dir /custom/path
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/fuckooredoo/
User configuration directory
.TP
.I ~/Downloads/
Default download directory
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TOR_SOCKS_PORT
Override default Tor SOCKS5 proxy port (default: 9050)
.TP
.B FUCKOOREDOO_DOWNLOAD_DIR
Set default download directory
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The application checks Tor connectivity on startup. If Tor is not running,
you will see an error message. Ensure Tor is installed and running:
.PP
.nf
    systemctl status tor
.fi
.PP
Check Tor connectivity:
.PP
.nf
    curl --socks5 127.0.0.1:9050 https://check.torproject.org
.fi
